<% title('About Password Pusher') %>
<h4 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>About</h4>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-8">
        <p>
            Password Pusher is an application to communicate passwords over the web. Links to passwords 
            expire after a certain number of views and/or time has passed.  Hosted at 
            <a href="https://pwpush.com" target="_blank">pwpush.com</a> or host your own.
        </p>

        <p>
            The source code to this site is <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher" target="_blank">on Github</a>.
            It’s opensource and free for anyone to use, review or modify. Deploy it to the cloud, internally at 
            your organization or just use <a href="https://pwpush.com" target="_blank">pwpush.com</a>. It’s up to you.</p>

        <h5 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>The Author</h5>

        <p>My name is Peter Giacomo Lombardo. You can find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterlombardo/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>,
         <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo" target="_blank">Github</a> or <a href="https://the0x00.dev" target="_blank">The OxOO</a>.</p>

        <p>For updates, you can <a href="https://twitter.com/pwpush" target="_blank">follow me on Twitter</a> or 
        <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo" target="_blank">Github</a>.</p>
        
        <h5 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>Contributors</h5>

        <p>Password Pusher has had a great community of contributors over the years. <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher/graphs/contributors" target="_blank">Take a look</a>.</p>

        <h5 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>Want to Help Out?</h5>

        <p><strong>By far the biggest help is to spread the word</strong>: Share and suggest Password Pusher to colleagues and friends.  
        If you are giving a presentation or writing a blog post, feel free to contact me for any questions.</p>

        <p>You can also:</p>
        <ol class="list-group list-group-numbered">
          <li class="list-group-item">
            Follow Password Pusher on <a href="https://twitter.com/pwpush" target="_blank">Twitter</a> or <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo" target="_blank">Github</a>
            and <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher" target="_blank">star the Github project</a>.
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            Code, documentation and 3rd party integrations are always welcome on <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher" target="_blank">Github</a>.
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            You could buy something at my <a href="https://oldschool.shopping" target="_blank">completely unrelated store</a>.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p class='mt-3'>Thank you for supporting Password Pusher!</p>

    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <h5 class="card-header"><em class="bi bi-stars"></em> Upcoming Birthday</h5>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Coming up on 10 Years</h5>
                <p class="card-text">The first git commit to Password Pusher was on <strong>December 28th, 2011</strong>. pwpush.com went live shortly thereafter.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <%= image_pack_tag 'media/img/pwpush_logo.png', class: 'card-img-top', alt: 'Password Pusher Logo' %>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">The Original Theme</h5>
                <p class="card-text">The original site design consisted of a dark background with a bold yellow font (<em>which admittedly I'm still a bit attached to</em>) but it was dated hence this new design you see now.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class='text-end'>Follow for news, changes & updates.</p>
        <div class="d-grid gap-2 d-md-block text-end mb-3">
            <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher" target="_blank"><button class="btn btn-primary" type="button"><em class="bi bi-github"></em></button></a>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/pwpush" target="_blank"><button class="btn btn-primary" type="button"><em class="bi bi-twitter"></em></button></a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
